headline: United Airlines Stock Soars as Earnings Smash Expectations. How It Hit a Revenue Record.
summary: United Airlines’ fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results soared past Wall Street’s expectations.  The carrier reported fourth-quarter adjusted earnings of $3.10 a share on revenue of $15.4 billion, up 4.8% and the highest quarterly revenue in United history, beating expectations.  Revenue of $59.07 billion, up 3.5% and the highest in United’s history, was slightly above the $59.05 billion expected.

headline: How Could Europe Retaliate Against Trump’s Tariffs Over Greenland?
summary: Hold off on implementing a trade deal with the U.S.: The European Union last summer agreed to a lopsided deal that included a 15% tariffs for most EU exports and a plan to eliminate tariffs on many American products.  The reduction in U.S. tariffs hasn’t yet far been ratified and is expected to be put on hold by the European Parliament in response to Trump’s tariff threat.  U.S. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent on Tuesday urged EU countries to stick to the trade deals forged with Washington, saying that “What President Trump is threatening on Greenland is very different than the other trade deals.”
